&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Third Executive Committee Meeting IEEE Ananthapuramu Subsection (ATPSS)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The IEEE Ananthapuramu Subsection in assocaition with JNTUA College of Engineering&amp;nbsp;has conducted three day International Conference on &amp;ldquo;System Automation, Reliability, Quality Control, Safety, Maintenance and Management (IC SARQCSMM19)&amp;rdquo; during 11-13th December 2019.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During the inaugural session, Patron, Principal, Prof. K. Govindarajulu, has presided over the function. Chief Patron, Vice-Chancellor, JNTUA Prof. S. Srinivas Kumar has appreciated the efforts of the team of officials who have taken the initiative in conducting 1&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt; International Conference in the campus. Sri. M. Srinivas Prasad, CEO &amp;amp; Founder, Educlo, Singapore, Guest of Honour has stated the importance of Educational cloud platform for providing access of e-learning sources world wide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prof. V. Sankar, Convener of the event has stated that 51 papers have been received, 28 have been accepted. The papers presented on the theme will be considered as a book series as Performability, Engineering, by Scrivener publications USA, in collaboration with John Wiley &amp;amp; Sons Inc. The papers on the any other theme will be published as proceeding of the Conference by the college JNTUA CEA with ISBN number.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chief Guest Sri G. Nageswara Rao, Chairman, Atomic Energy Regulatory Board (AERB), Mumbai has enlightened about the importance of atomic energy as a alternate energy in the future which is going to be part of green energy revolution which is less harmful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Parton and Rector JNTUA has discussed about safety aspects in environmental conditions&lt;/p&gt;
